  "text": "Monocytes were isolated from source leukocyte packs obtained from the American Red Cross as described previously [CITATION_1] . Monocytes used in real time PCR experiments and transfection experiments were purified by positive selection using CD14 Monocyte Isolation Kit from Miltenyi Biotech (Auburn, CA) (.90% pure). In some experiments, monocytes were isolated by clumping method (70% pure). To obtain monocyte-derived macrophages (MDMs), monocytes were cultured in RPMI-1640 medium containing 10% FBS, and 10 mg/ml polymyxin B and 20 ng/ml M-CSF.",
